6-09-19T11:13:21.293Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/576287/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/576287/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/576287/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2016-09-05","Overseas Aid","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what were (1) the core, and (2) the non-core, contributions made by the Department for International Development to (a) the United Nations Population Fund, (b) UNICEF, (c) the World Health Organization, (d) the Joint United Nations Programme on HIV/AIDS, (e) UN Women, (f) The Global Fund, (g) the International Planned Parenthood Federation, and (h) Women and Children First (UK), in (i) 2014–15, and (ii) 2015–16.","false","Biography information for Baroness Tonge",,"Baroness Tonge","HL1527"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/576288","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-09-14","<p>Ascent Flight Training charges approximately £610,000 to train each fast jet student pilot to the point where they are ready to move on to the Operational Conversion Unit stage.</p>",,"Earl Howe",,"2016-09-14T15:27:57.897Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/576288/answer","Biography information for Earl Howe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/576288/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/576288/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-09-05","Military Aircraft: Training","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government how much Ascent Flight Training charges the Ministry of Defence to train a fast jet pilot to the point where they are ready to move on to the Operational Conversion Unit of their chosen aircraft.","false","Biography information for Lord West of Spithead",,"Lord West of Spithead","HL1528"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/576289","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-09-13","<p>It is anticipated that 118 fixed wing jet trainees will graduate from the Ascent Flight Training programme between 2016 and 2019. All elements of the recently contracted UK Military Flying Training System are due to be fully up and running by April 2019.</p>",,"Earl Howe",,"2016-09-13T15:53:44.403Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/576289/answer","Biography information for Earl Howe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/576289/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/576289/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-09-05","Military Aircraft: Training","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government how many fixed-wing jet trainees are projected to graduate from the Ascent Flight Training programme between 2016 and 2019; and when the programme is due to be fully up and running.","false","Biography information for Lord West of Spithead",,"Lord West of Spithead","HL1529"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/576290","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-09-14","<p>Up to June 2015, £308,000 was deducted from payments to Ascent Flight Training. No further deductions have been made since that time.</p>",,"Earl Howe",,"2016-09-14T15:26:17.29Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/576290/answer","Biography information for Earl Howe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/576290/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/576290/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-09-05","Military Aircraft: Training","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government how much Ascent Flight Training has been fined for failing to deliver an adequate service since it signed the 25-year contract with the Ministry of Defence.","false","Biography information for Lord West of Spithead",,"Lord West of Spithead","HL1530"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/576291","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-09-12","<p>HMS AMBUSH is undergoing repairs at Her Majesty's Naval Base Clyde.</p><p>It is UK policy that we do not comment on matters relating to submarine activity or operations as this would, or would be likely to, prejudice the capability, effectiveness or security of the Armed Forces.</p>",,"Earl Howe",,"2016-09-12T14:55:17.583Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/576291/answer","Biography information for Earl Howe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/576291/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/576291/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-09-05","HMS Ambush","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government when they plan HMS Ambush to be fully operational.","false","Biography information for Lord West of Spithead",,"Lord West of Spithead","HL1531"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/576292","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-09-13","<p>HMS OCEAN entered service in 1998 with an expected in service life of 20 years and she will decommission in 2018. The Strategic Defence Security Review 2015 made provision to augment the Queen Elizabeth Class carriers and maximise their ability to support amphibious operations. Prior to the carriers being brought into service, other Royal Navy and Royal Fleet Auxiliary ships will provide support to amphibious operations.</p>",,"Earl Howe",,"2016-09-13T15:53:05.767Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/576292/answer","Biography information for Earl Howe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/576292/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/576292/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-09-05","HMS Ocean","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what is the planned out-of-service date for HMS Ocean, and how her landing platform helicopter capabilities will be provided prior to the entry into service of HMS Prince of Wales.","false","Biography information for Lord West of Spithead",,"Lord West of Spithead","HL1532"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/576293","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-09-12","<p>In August 2014, the Ministry of Defence placed a contract valued at £348 million with BAE Systems on the Clyde for the procurement of three River Class Offshore Patrol Vessels (OPVs). On current plans, we expect these three vessels to enter service between 2018 and 2019.</p><p>The Strategic Defence and Security Review 2015 set out the Government's plan to build two additional OPVs and we have begun the planning work necessary to contract for these additional ships. As with all equipment procurement programmes, the cost and schedule are set at the main investment decision, and we have not yet reached that decision point.</p>",,"Earl Howe",,"2016-09-12T14:55:59.907Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/576293/answer","Biography information for Earl Howe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/576293/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/576293/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-09-05","Patrol Craft","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what are the planned in-service dates for the offshore patrol vessels presently on order or planned; and how much each vessel will cost.","false","Biography information for Lord West of Spithead",,"Lord West of Spithead","HL1533"
